summary: Entertainment Weekly’s Captain Marvel Exclusive Paging Carol Danvers. Captain Marvel is on the cover of Entertainment Weekly’s...
caption:
Entertainment Weekly’s Captain Marvel Exclusive

Paging Carol Danvers.

Captain Marvel is on the cover of Entertainment Weekly’s latest issue, and we’ve got the first look at Brie Larson’s part-Kree, part-human hero. Audiences briefly saw Carol’s symbol in the end-credits scene of Avengers: Infinity War, but come March 2019, the Air Force pilot with alien powers will be getting her own origin story.

Not only is Captain Marvel the first solo, female-led movie in the Marvel Cinematic Universe, but it’s an introduction to the most powerful hero the MCU has ever seen. (Another Marvel first: It’s set in the 1990s!) Click through for an in-depth look at all things Carol — as well as an introduction to a few of her friends and foes.

https://ew.com/movies/captain-marvel-first-look-images/

summary:
Kevin Feige recently talked about the futur of female-heros movies with EW :  
“With [Ant-Man and The Wasp] and now with Captain...
caption:
Kevin Feige recently talked about the futur of female-heros movies with EW :

“With [Ant-Man and The Wasp] and now with Captain Marvel and many movies to be announced in the near future, I’m anxious for the time where it’s not a novelty that there is a female-led superhero movie, but it is a norm. And it is less a story of, ‘Oh, look, a female hero,’ and it’s more a story of, ‘Oh, what’s this about? Who’s this character? I’m excited to see that.’ And I think we can get there.”

Kevin Feige a récemment discuté des films de super-héroïnes avec EW:

“Avec Ant-Man and The Wasp et maintenant avec Captain Marvel et d'autres films qui seront annoncées dans peu de temps, je suis impatient d'arriver à point ou se ne sera pas une nouveauté d'avoir une femme en tant que personnage principal mais que se sera totalement normal. Que se serait moins ‘Oh, regardez, c'est une femme-héro’ et plus 'Oh, qui est ce personnage ? Qu'elle est son histoire ? Je veux en savoir plus!’. Je pense vraiment qu'on peut y arriver.”
